## Brief Overview {#brief-overview}

The annual Free and Open Source Software for Geospatial Europe (FOSS4GE) conference, a European offshoot of the Open Source Geospatial Foundation (OSGeo) conference, is a volunteer-driven community event. Its core mission is to cultivate a diverse and sustainable open community, fostering knowledge sharing and collaborative learning. While software serves as the initial connection, it's a shared commitment to societal and environmental well-being, striving to solve global challenges incrementally, that truly unites its participants.

We are proposing, on behalf of West University of Timisoara and in partnership with [geo-spatial.org](http://geo-spatial.org) to host the FOSS4G Europe 2026 conference in Timisoara, Romania, confident in the profound societal impact it can have both locally and regionally.

Timisoara and its surrounding region has a unique history within Romania. Over centuries, it was a point of contention for various states \- Roman, Hungarian, Ottoman, Austrian \- each leaving visible marks. This rich history has shaped a remarkably multicultural society, serving as a beautiful testament to harmony within Romania and the Balkans (it's located just 50 km from Serbia). The open-mindedness of its inhabitants is likely a key factor in its role as the birthplace of Romania's anti-Communist movement and its current status as one of the country's most economically advanced areas. In recognition of its cultural significance, Timisoara was designated the European Cultural Capital for 2023\. We encourage you to seize this opportunity to expand your knowledge and forge connections with esteemed colleagues from across the globe.

This proposal is only valid for the FOSS4G Europe 2026\. Based on future conditions we might consider applying for future events.
